{
  "text": "The ability of ANG II to stimulate Na ϩ /H ϩ exchange has been observed previously in vascular smooth muscle and other tissues [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In a number of tissues, the stimulation of Na ϩ /H ϩ exchange by ANG II is thought to involve activation of protein kinase C (11). Mechanistically, ANG II has been reported to stimulate Na ϩ /H ϩ exchange partly as a result of a reduction in the K m for external sodium (7) and also through an increase of V max that may be, in part, the result of a rise in the number of Na ϩ /H ϩ exchanger sites on the plasma membrane [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Although the observed increase of cytoplasmic sodium concentration suggests that Na ϩ /H ϩ exchange-mediated proton export is stimulated in ANG II-treated NPE cells, no detectable increase of pH i was observed in cells exposed to ANG II.",
  "correct_citation": {
